text: confession: i lied in <#C0260V1C3>, i once ate an ant on top of a fallen jolly rancher when i was a kid (i don’t remember doing this, but my brother and sister always bring it up to me)

confession: In high school I would call myself in sick when my dad was out of town saying it was an Aunt. The crabby lady in charge of attendance once called me out on it, and i said “yeah people always say we sound alike”. Never got in trouble.
if that happened to me, i would’ve hung up the phone
Also never got caught for having a nose piercing. Went to a catholic all-girls school.

confession: the first time i ever used photoshop was to photoshop my report card in middle school. i changed my grades to all As, and my dad gave me $50 for it. one of the biggest regrets i still live with, still feel super guilty.

another note: i didn’t have a scanner at the time, so i had to have a friend scan hers and i had to photoshop her name and address out of it and put mine in.
to be fair, you probably learned more applicable skills from that than social studies
